class='comment_text entry-content'><p>Looking for an easy way to keep your server running when you exit the shell?</p><p>Get the screen command via<br
/> apt-get install screen</p><p>Then run FedOne prefixed by the screen command<br
/> screen ./run-server.sh</p><p>Exit out of the screen by pressing Ctrl+a followed by d.<br
/> You can reattach to the screen via<br
/> screen -r</p><p>Or just exit the console. The server will continue to run!</p><p>Courtesy of:<br
/> <a
href="http://www.wiseguysonly.com/2009/10/14/keep-linux-scripts-running-after-you-have-closed-a-remote-shell/" rel="nofollow">http://www.wiseguysonly.com/2009/10/14/keep-linux-scripts-running-after-you-have-closed-a-remote-shell/</a></p> <a
